## File Locations

- **Pipeline State:** `D:\BDArchitect-DetailLibrary-2025\pipeline_state.json`
- **Captures:** `D:\BDArchitect-DetailLibrary-2025\captures\`
- **Custom Pipelines:** `D:\BDArchitect-DetailLibrary-2025\pipelines\`

---

## Creating Custom Pipelines

Save a JSON file in `D:\BDArchitect-DetailLibrary-2025\pipelines\`:

```json
{
  "Id": "my-pipeline",
  "Name": "My Custom Pipeline",
  "Description": "Description of what it does",
  "Phases": [
    {
      "Name": "Phase 1",
      "Description": "First phase",
      "RequiresApproval": false,
      "Steps": [
        {
          "Name": "Step 1",
          "Action": "getDocumentInfo",
          "Parameters": {},
          "CaptureAfter": true,
          "Verification": {
            "Type": "exists",
            "Query": "getDocumentInfo",
            "Property": "projectInfo"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "Name": "Phase 2",
      "RequiresApproval": true,
      "Steps": [...]
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Integration with Other Skills

This pipeline system can call any registered MCP method. Combine with:
- `bd-project-init` - Use new-project pipeline
- `cd-set-assembly` - Use cd-assembly pipeline
- `bim-quality-validator` - Use qc-review pipeline

The autonomous system handles the orchestration - you just approve checkpoints.
